          <div><strong>A lapsed CP12 blocks a Section 21 notice</strong><p>Courts have ruled that CP12 compliance is a legal prerequisite for a valid Section 21. A lapsed or unserved certificate can prevent eviction proceedings entirely. Annual renewal and same-day forwarding to tenants protects your Section 21 position on Formby rental properties.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">3</div>
          <div><strong>Certificate must be provided to tenants within 28 days</strong><p>You must provide a copy of the valid CP12 to existing tenants within 28 days of issue and to new tenants before they move in. We email the digital certificate the same day so you can forward it to Formby tenants immediately.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-who-item" style="border-left:3px solid #dc2626;">
          <div style="background:#dc2626;color:#ffffff;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:900;font-size:1rem;min-width:1.75rem;height:1.75rem;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">4</div>
          <div><strong>Certificate must be renewed every 12 months</strong><p>A CP12 is valid for 12 months. Renewed between 10 and 12 months after the previous one, the new certificate runs from the old expiry date, preserving the full 12 months. We add all Formby landlords to our annual reminder list.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


