        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas leak check</strong><p>All pipework and appliance connections tested for gas leaks using calibrated detection equipment. Any leak classified under the Gas Industry Unsafe Situations Procedure and addressed before we leave.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue integrity and combustion products</strong><p>All flues tested for integrity and safe discharge of combustion gases. For Formby coastal properties, external flue terminals checked for condition and corrosion.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Ventilation adequacy</strong><p>All gas appliances checked for adequate ventilation. Particularly relevant for gas hobs in refitted kitchens where original ventilation may have been altered during renovation work.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Safety device operation</strong><p>All appliance safety devices tested individually. Flame failure devices on gas hobs and gas fires tested. Each must demonstrate correct operation before the appliance can pass the inspection.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Signs of incomplete combustion</strong><p>Checked for staining, sooting or carbon deposits around all appliances. More common in gas fires and older appliances than in modern sealed flue boilers.</p></div></div>
